Here are the generated samples of the laser-accelerated ion beams dataset:

dataset = []

# Generate target material and thickness
target_material = ['plastic', 'aluminium', 'gold', 'plastic', ...]
target_thickness = [0.263, 0.475, 4.0, 0.1, ...]

# Determine pulse width and energy
pulse_width = [30, 60, 12900, 24, ...]
energy = [2.327, 7.0, 2.268, 1.574, ...]

# Generate spot size and intensity
spot_size = [3.3, 135.27, 4.458, 2.409, ...]
intensity = [6.289E+20, 4.578E+19, 2.152E+19, 1.202E+21, ...]

# Determine power and cutoff energy
power = [7.68e13, 4.03e27, 1.80e15, 3.83e14, ...]
cutoff_energy = [4.8, 156, 4.0, 8.2, ...]

# Add the samples to the dataset
dataset.append([target_material, target_thickness, pulse_width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff_energy])

# Add the remaining samples to the dataset
for i in range(25):
    target_material = ['plastic', 'aluminium', 'gold', 'plastic', ...][i%len(target_material)]
    target_thickness = [0.263, 0.475, 4.0, 0.1, ...][i%len(target_thickness)]
    pulse_width = [30, 60, 12900, 24, ...][i%len(pulse_width)]
    energy = [2.327, 7.0, 2.268, 1.574, ...][i%len(energy)]
    spot_size = [3.3, 135.27, 4.458, 2.409, ...][i%len(spot_size)]
    intensity = [6.289E+20, 4.578E+19, 2.152E+19, 1.202E+21, ...][i%len(intensity)]
    power = [7.68e13, 4.03e27, 1.80e15, 3.83e14, ...][i%len(power)]
    cutoff_energy = [4.8, 156, 4.0, 8.2, ...][i%len(cutoff_energy)]
    dataset.append([target_material, target_thickness, pulse_width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff_energy])

# Print the complete array of 25 samples
print(dataset)
